  "content": {
    "prompt": "<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">A beam consisting of electrons with energy <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"E\"><math alttext=\"E\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi>E</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> is incident on a single slit <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"X\"><math alttext=\"X\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mtext>X</mtext></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>. The diffraction pattern is observed. Slit <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"X\"><math alttext=\"X\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mstyle><mrow><mtext>X</mtext></mrow></mstyle></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> is then replaced by slit <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"Y\"><math alttext=\"Y\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mtext>Y</mtext></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>, and the new diffraction pattern is observed to have fringes that are farther apart than those in the first pattern. Which of the following is a possible explanation for why the spacings are different?</p>\n",
